Energi Mega, London Sumatra, Samudera: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-04-05T01:28:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/energi-mega-london-sumatra-samudera-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 0.2 percent to 3,700.05.  Energy companies: Crude oil for May delivery declined for
the first time in four days, falling as much as 0.4 percent to
$108.07 a barrel in after-hours trading in  New York  as of 8:08
a.m. Jakarta time.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, rose 1.8 percent to 2,900 rupiah and
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, was
unchanged at 128 rupiah.  Rubber producers: Rubber futures in  Tokyo  rose as much as
4.5 percent to 464.1 yen a kilogram, the highest level since
March 7. The September-delivery contract traded at 459.9 yen at
9:07 a.m. Tokyo time.  PT Perusahaan Perkebunan London Sumatra  Indonesia  (LSIP
IJ), the nation’s second-largest listed plantation company by
market value, fell 1.1 percent to 2,325 rupiah and PT Bakrie
Sumatera Plantations (UNSP IJ) was unchanged at 360 rupiah.  PT Samudera Indonesia (SMDR IJ): The shipping company has
received 1 trillion rupiah ($115 million) of bank loans to fund
its capital expenditure this year, Investor Daily reported,
citing Director Iryanto Hutagaol. Samudera hopes to boost
revenue by 20 percent this year, from 4.33 trillion rupiah last
year, the report said. The stock rose 2 percent to 3,875 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net 
